"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkmy_docusaurus=globalThis.webpackChunkmy_docusaurus||[]).push([[9724],{6048(n){n.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/blog/Java-overview","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/Java-overview","source":"@site/blog/blog/Java-overview.mdx","title":"blog/Java-overview","description":"slug: tim-hieu-Java-platform","date":"2026-02-12T04:20:34.063Z","tags":[],"readingTime":4.54,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus"}},"content":"slug: tim-hieu-Java-platform\\r\\ntitle: T\xecm hi\u1ec3u Java Platform \u2013 Execution Flow & JVM Architecture\\r\\ndate: 2026-02-12\\r\\ntags: [java, jvm, bytecode, jdk, jre, jit, execution-flow]\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 1. Java Platform Overview \u2013 T\u1ed5ng quan n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng Java\\r\\n\\r\\nJava kh\xf4ng ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 **m\u1ed9t ng\xf4n ng\u1eef l\u1eadp tr\xecnh**, m\xe0 l\xe0 **m\u1ed9t n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh (Java Platform)**.\\r\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 Khi n\xf3i *\u201cl\u1eadp tr\xecnh Java\u201d*, th\u1ef1c ch\u1ea5t ta \u0111ang l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c v\u1edbi **3 th\xe0nh ph\u1ea7n c\u1ed1t l\xf5i**:\\r\\n\\r\\n- **Java Language**\\r\\n- **JVM (Java Virtual Machine)**\\r\\n- **H\u1ec7 sinh th\xe1i th\u01b0 vi\u1ec7n & c\xf4ng c\u1ee5**\\r\\n\\r\\n### M\u1ee5c ti\xeau c\u1ed1t l\xf5i c\u1ee7a Java\\r\\n\\r\\n> **Write Once, Run Anywhere (WORA)**\\r\\n\\r\\nVi\u1ebft code **m\u1ed9t l\u1ea7n**, ch\u1ea1y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tr\xean:\\r\\n- Windows\\r\\n- Linux\\r\\n- macOS  \\r\\n\u2026 m\xe0 **kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n s\u1eeda code**\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 2. Vai tr\xf2 c\u1ee7a JDK, JRE, JVM\\r\\n\\r\\nR\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi h\u1ecdc Java **b\u1ecb nh\u1ea7m l\u1eabn 3 kh\xe1i ni\u1ec7m n\xe0y**, n\xean c\u1ea7n l\xe0m r\xf5 tuy\u1ec7t \u0111\u1ed1i.\\r\\n\\r\\n### 2.1 JVM \u2013 Java Virtual Machine\\r\\n\\r\\n**JVM l\xe0 g\xec?**\\r\\n\\r\\n- JVM l\xe0 **m\xe1y \u1ea3o**\\r\\n- Ch\u1ea1y **bytecode Java**\\r\\n- \u0110\xf3ng vai tr\xf2 **trung gian gi\u1eefa Java v\xe0 h\u1ec7 \u0111i\u1ec1u h\xe0nh**\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc JVM:\\r\\n- Kh\xf4ng hi\u1ec3u `.java`\\r\\n- Kh\xf4ng hi\u1ec3u `.exe`\\r\\n- **Ch\u1ec9 hi\u1ec3u `.class` (bytecode)**\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 M\u1ed7i h\u1ec7 \u0111i\u1ec1u h\xe0nh c\xf3 **JVM ri\xeang**, nh\u01b0ng:\\r\\n- Bytecode th\xec **gi\u1ed1ng nhau**\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n### 2.2 JRE \u2013 Java Runtime Environment\\r\\n\\r\\n**JRE g\u1ed3m:**\\r\\n\\r\\n- JVM\\r\\n- Core Java Libraries (java.lang, java.util, ...)\\r\\n- C\xe1c file c\u1ea5u h\xecnh runtime\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 JRE d\xf9ng \u0111\u1ec3:\\r\\n- **Ch\u1ea1y ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh Java**\\r\\n- \u274c Kh\xf4ng d\xf9ng \u0111\u1ec3 vi\u1ebft hay bi\xean d\u1ecbch code\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc N\u1ebfu m\xe1y ch\u1ec9 c\xf3 JRE:\\r\\n- Ch\u1ea1y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c `.class`\\r\\n- \u274c Kh\xf4ng bi\xean d\u1ecbch \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c `.java`\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n### 2.3 JDK \u2013 Java Development Kit\\r\\n\\r\\n**JDK = JRE + C\xf4ng c\u1ee5 ph\xe1t tri\u1ec3n**\\r\\n\\r\\nBao g\u1ed3m:\\r\\n- `javac` (compiler)\\r\\n- `java` (launcher)\\r\\n- `javadoc`, `jdb`, ...\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 JDK d\xf9ng \u0111\u1ec3:\\r\\n- Vi\u1ebft code\\r\\n- Bi\xean d\u1ecbch\\r\\n- Ch\u1ea1y\\r\\n- Debug\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Khi c\xe0i Java \u0111\u1ec3 h\u1ecdc l\u1eadp tr\xecnh:\\r\\n\u27a1\ufe0f **LU\xd4N c\u1ea7n JDK**\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n### 2.4 M\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 t\u1ed5ng th\u1ec3\\r\\nJDK <br />\\r\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 JRE <br />\\r\\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 JVM <br />\\r\\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Java Core Libraries <br />\\r\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Development Tools <br />\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n## 3. M\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 gi\u1eefa Java Language v\xe0 Java Platform\\r\\n### Java Language\\r\\n- C\xfa ph\xe1p v\xe0 t\u1eeb kh\xf3a\\r\\n- Ki\u1ec3u d\u1eef li\u1ec7u\\r\\n- OOP (class, object, inheritance)\\r\\n- File m\xe3 ngu\u1ed3n `.java`\\r\\n\\r\\n### Java Platform\\r\\n- JVM (Java Virtual Machine)\\r\\n- ClassLoader Subsystem\\r\\n- Runtime Data Areas\\r\\n- Execution Engine & Garbage Collector\\r\\n\\r\\n**Java Language ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 ph\u1ea7n n\u1ed5i**  \\r\\n **Java Platform m\u1edbi l\xe0 th\u1ee9 quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh ch\u1ea1y th\u1ebf n\xe0o**\\r\\n\\r\\n ---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 4. Java Execution Flow \u2013 Lu\u1ed3ng th\u1ef1c thi c\u1ee7a Java\\r\\n\\r\\nKhi b\u1ea1n ch\u1ea1y m\u1ed9t ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh Java, **JVM kh\xf4ng th\u1ef1c thi tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp file `.java`**.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Lu\u1ed3ng t\u1ed5ng qu\xe1t\\r\\n\\r\\nIDE  <br />\\r\\n\u2193 (Save)  <br />\\r\\n`Hello.java` (\u1ed4 c\u1ee9ng) <br /> \\r\\n\u2193 (Compile)  <br />\\r\\n`javac Hello.java`  <br />\\r\\n\u2193  <br />\\r\\n`Hello.class` (Bytecode)  <br />\\r\\n\u2193  <br />\\r\\nJVM (RAM)  <br />\\r\\n\u2193  <br />\\r\\nOS  <br />\\r\\n\u2193  <br />\\r\\nCPU th\u1ef1c thi  <br />\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 5. Compile-time v\xe0 Runtime trong Java\\r\\n\\r\\n### 5.1 Compile-time\\r\\n\\r\\n**X\u1ea3y ra khi ch\u1ea1y:**\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\njavac Hello.java\\r\\n```\\r\\n\u0110\u1ea7u v\xe0o:\\r\\n\\r\\nFile .java (source code)\\r\\n\\r\\nJava l\xe0m g\xec?\\r\\n-Ki\u1ec3m tra c\xfa ph\xe1p\\r\\n-Ki\u1ec3m tra ki\u1ec3u d\u1eef li\u1ec7u\\r\\n-Bi\xean d\u1ecbch sang bytecode\\r\\n\\r\\n\u0110\u1ea7u ra:\\r\\n-File .class\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Compile-time kh\xf4ng ch\u1ea1y ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh\\r\\n\\r\\n### 5.2 Runtime\\r\\n\\r\\nX\u1ea3y ra khi ch\u1ea1y:\\r\\n```bash\\r\\njava Hello\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\u0110\u1ea7u v\xe0o:\\r\\n-File .class\\r\\n\\r\\nJava l\xe0m g\xec?\\r\\n-JVM load class\\r\\n-Ki\u1ec3m tra bytecode\\r\\n\\r\\nTh\u1ef1c thi\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Runtime m\u1edbi l\xe0 l\xfac ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh th\u1ef1c s\u1ef1 ch\u1ea1y\\r\\n\\r\\n## 6. Bytecode l\xe0 g\xec? V\xec sao Java portable?\\r\\n\\r\\nBytecode l\xe0 g\xec?\\r\\n-L\xe0 m\xe3 trung gian\\r\\n-Kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i m\xe3 m\xe1y\\r\\n-Kh\xf4ng ph\u1ee5 thu\u1ed9c OS hay CPU\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Bytecode:\\r\\n-Ch\u1ea1y tr\xean JVM\\r\\n-JVM d\u1ecbch ti\u1ebfp sang m\xe3 m\xe1y\\r\\n\\r\\nV\xec sao Java ch\u1ea1y \u0111a n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng?\\r\\n\\r\\nJava Source (.java)<br />\\r\\n        \u2193<br />\\r\\n   Bytecode (.class)<br />\\r\\n        \u2193<br />\\r\\n \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510 <br />\\r\\n \u2502 JVM Windows \u2502 \u2192 CPU Windows <br />\\r\\n \u2502 JVM Linux   \u2502 \u2192 CPU Linux <br />\\r\\n \u2502 JVM macOS   \u2502 \u2192 CPU macOS <br />\\r\\n \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 Kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i Java ch\u1ea1y tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp tr\xean OS\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 JVM m\u1edbi l\xe0 th\u1ee9 ch\u1ea1y tr\xean OS\\r\\n\\r\\n## 7. JVM Architecture \u2013 Ki\u1ebfn tr\xfac JVM\\r\\n\\r\\nJVM g\u1ed3m 3 kh\u1ed1i l\u1edbn:\\r\\n-ClassLoader Subsystem\\r\\n-Runtime Data Areas\\r\\n-Execution Engine\\r\\n\\r\\n## 8. ClassLoader Subsystem\\r\\n\\r\\nNhi\u1ec7m v\u1ee5:\\r\\n-Load .class v\xe0o JVM\\r\\n-Ki\u1ec3m tra t\xednh h\u1ee3p l\u1ec7\\r\\n-Chu\u1ea9n b\u1ecb class \u0111\u1ec3 ch\u1ea1y\\r\\n\\r\\n### C\xe1c lo\u1ea1i ClassLoader trong JVM\\r\\n\\r\\n- **Bootstrap ClassLoader**  \\r\\n  Load c\xe1c core class c\u1ee7a Java (v\xed d\u1ee5: `java.lang`, `java.util`)\\r\\n\\r\\n- **Platform ClassLoader** *(Java 9+)*  \\r\\n  Load c\xe1c th\u01b0 vi\u1ec7n thu\u1ed9c Java Platform (v\xed d\u1ee5: `java.sql`, `java.xml`)\\r\\n\\r\\n- **Application ClassLoader**  \\r\\n  Load c\xe1c class do l\u1eadp tr\xecnh vi\xean vi\u1ebft (classpath)\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Class ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c load khi c\u1ea7n thi\u1ebft\\r\\n\\r\\n## 9. Runtime Data Areas \u2013 V\xf9ng nh\u1edb trong JVM\\r\\n\\r\\n### 9.1 Method Area\\r\\n\\r\\nL\u01b0u:\\r\\n-Class metadata\\r\\n-Method info\\r\\n-Static variables\\r\\n\\r\\n### 9.2 Heap\\r\\n\\r\\n-L\u01b0u object\\r\\n-D\xf9ng chung cho to\xe0n JVM\\r\\n-Do Garbage Collector qu\u1ea3n l\xfd\\r\\n\\r\\n### 9.3 Stack\\r\\n\\r\\nM\u1ed7i thread c\xf3 stack ri\xeang\\r\\n\\r\\nL\u01b0u:\\r\\n-Local variables\\r\\n-Method call\\r\\n-Reference\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Stack nh\u1ecf, nhanh\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Heap l\u1edbn, ch\u1eadm h\u01a1n\\r\\n\\r\\n### 9.4 PC Register\\r\\n\\r\\nL\u01b0u \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 instruction \u0111ang ch\u1ea1y\\r\\n\\r\\n### 9.5 Native Method Stack\\r\\n\\r\\nD\xf9ng cho code native (C/C++)\\r\\n\\r\\n## 10. Execution Engine \u2013 B\u1ed9 m\xe1y th\u1ef1c thi\\r\\n### 10.1 Interpreter\\r\\n\\r\\n\u0110\u1ecdc bytecode\\r\\n\\r\\nTh\u1ef1c thi t\u1eebng instruction\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc \u01afu \u0111i\u1ec3m:\\r\\n-Ch\u1ea1y ngay\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc Nh\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111i\u1ec3m:\\r\\n-Ch\u1eadm n\u1ebfu ch\u1ea1y l\u1eb7p nhi\u1ec1u l\u1ea7n\\r\\n\\r\\n### 10.2 JIT Compiler (Just-In-Time)\\r\\n\\r\\nJIT l\xe0m g\xec?\\r\\n-Ph\xe1t hi\u1ec7n \u0111o\u1ea1n code ch\u1ea1y nhi\u1ec1u\\r\\n-Bi\xean d\u1ecbch bytecode \u2192 m\xe3 m\xe1y\\r\\n-Cache l\u1ea1i \u0111\u1ec3 d\xf9ng sau\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc JVM hi\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ea1i:\\r\\n-Interpreter + JIT\\r\\n-T\u1ef1 t\u1ed1i \u01b0u khi ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh ch\u1ea1y\\r\\n\\r\\n## 11. T\u1ed5ng k\u1ebft\\r\\n\\r\\nTham kh\u1ea3o slide chi ti\u1ebft t\u1ea1i \u0111\xe2y :\\r\\n- \ud83d\udd17 https://www.canva.com/design/DAHApyPYZmw/AQAchpZL_3B77rpOe4-3YQ/edit\\r\\n\\r\\nJava kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01a1n thu\u1ea7n l\xe0 m\u1ed9t ng\xf4n ng\u1eef, m\xe0 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh g\u1ed3m JDK, JRE v\xe0 JVM. Ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh Java kh\xf4ng ch\u1ea1y tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp tr\xean h\u1ec7 \u0111i\u1ec1u h\xe0nh m\xe0 ph\u1ea3i tr\u1ea3i qua qu\xe1 tr\xecnh bi\xean d\u1ecbch sang bytecode, sau \u0111\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c JVM th\xf4ng d\u1ecbch v\xe0 t\u1ed1i \u01b0u b\u1eb1ng JIT tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi CPU th\u1ef1c thi.\\r\\n\\r\\nVi\u1ec7c hi\u1ec3u r\xf5:\\r\\n\\r\\n-Java Platform <br/>\\r\\n-Execution Flow <br/>\\r\\n-JVM Architecture <br/>\\r\\n\\r\\ngi\xfap l\u1eadp tr\xecnh vi\xean:\\r\\n\\r\\n-Hi\u1ec3u s\xe2u b\u1ea3n ch\u1ea5t Java <br/>\\r\\n-Debug t\u1ed1t h\u01a1n <br/>\\r\\n-Vi\u1ebft code t\u1ed1i \u01b0u h\u01a1n <br/>\\r\\n-C\xf3 n\u1ec1n t\u1ea3ng h\u1ecdc Spring, JVM tuning, backend chuy\xean s\xe2u <br/>"},{"id":"huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus","source":"@site/blog/huong-dan-dung-blog.mdx","title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","description":"1. Blog l\xe0 g\xec? Docusaurus l\xe0 g\xec?","date":"2026-02-12T03:42:30.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.67,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","slug":"huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"blog/Java-overview","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/Java-overview"},"nextItem":{"title":"Java-overview","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/Java-overview"}},"content":"## 1. Blog l\xe0 g\xec? Docusaurus l\xe0 g\xec?\\r\\n\\r\\n**Blog** l\xe0 n\u01a1i chia s\u1ebb ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c, ghi ch\xe9p qu\xe1 tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp.  \\r\\n**Docusaurus** l\xe0 framework gi\xfap t\u1ea1o website blog / docs nhanh, \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng tr\xean React.\\r\\n\\r\\n## 2. C\xf4ng c\u1ee5 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng\\r\\n- NodeJS  \\r\\n- VS Code  \\r\\n- Docusaurus  \\r\\n- GitHub Pages  \\r\\n\\r\\n## 3. Quy tr\xecnh d\u1ef1ng Blog\\r\\n\\r\\nSlide d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y m\xf4 t\u1ea3 **to\xe0n b\u1ed9 quy tr\xecnh x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng website**,  \\r\\nt\u1eeb b\u01b0\u1edbc kh\u1edfi t\u1ea1o project cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi deploy (tri\u1ec3n khai) website l\xean GitHub Pages.\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 **Xem slide h\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn chi ti\u1ebft t\u1ea1i \u0111\xe2y:**  \\r\\n\ud83d\udd17 https://www.canva.com/design/DAG-x-HN2J0/AXmxIe_VDDip6aalEPP8PQ/view\\r\\n\\r\\n*(Slide s\u1ebd m\u1edf \u1edf tab m\u1edbi \u0111\u1ec3 xem \u0111\u1ea7y \u0111\u1ee7 v\xe0 r\xf5 r\xe0ng h\u01a1n)*\\r\\n\\r\\n## 4. K\u1ebft lu\u1eadn\\r\\n\\r\\nSau khi xem slide, ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi c\xf3 th\u1ec3:\\r\\n- T\u1ea1o project Docusaurus  \\r\\n- Vi\u1ebft b\xe0i blog  \\r\\n- \u0110\u1ea9y source code l\xean GitHub  \\r\\n- Deploy website b\u1eb1ng GitHub Pages"},{"id":"/Java-overview","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/Java-overview","source":"@site/blog/Java-overview.mdx","title":"Java-overview","description":"","date":"2026-02-12T03:42:30.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus"},"nextItem":{"title":"Blockchain & Web3 \u2013 H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1eeb c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n \u0111\u1ebfn th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/blockchain-web3"}},"content":""},{"id":"/blog/blockchain-web3","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/blockchain-web3","source":"@site/blog/blog/blockchain-web3.mdx","title":"Blockchain & Web3 \u2013 H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1eeb c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n \u0111\u1ebfn th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh","description":"Gi\u1ea3i th\xedch Blockchain, Web3, Smart Contract v\xe0 v\xed Web3 m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch d\u1ec5 hi\u1ec3u cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u","date":"2026-02-08T03:30:18.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.99,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Blockchain & Web3 \u2013 H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1eeb c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n \u0111\u1ebfn th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh","description":"Gi\u1ea3i th\xedch Blockchain, Web3, Smart Contract v\xe0 v\xed Web3 m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch d\u1ec5 hi\u1ec3u cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Java-overview","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/Java-overview"},"nextItem":{"title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus"}},"content":"## \ud83d\udccc Gi\u1edbi thi\u1ec7u\\r\\n\\r\\nBlockchain v\xe0 Web3 \u0111ang l\xe0 nh\u1eefng c\xf4ng ngh\u1ec7 c\u1ed1t l\xf5i c\u1ee7a Internet th\u1ebf h\u1ec7 m\u1edbi.  \\r\\nN\u1ebfu Web2 gi\xfap ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng **t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\xe1c v\xe0 t\u1ea1o n\u1ed9i dung**, th\xec Web3 h\u01b0\u1edbng \u0111\u1ebfn m\u1ee5c ti\xeau l\u1edbn h\u01a1n:  \\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 **trao quy\u1ec1n s\u1edf h\u1eefu d\u1eef li\u1ec7u v\xe0 t\xe0i s\u1ea3n s\u1ed1 cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng**.\\r\\n\\r\\nB\xe0i vi\u1ebft n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf d\xe0nh cho **ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u**, gi\xfap b\u1ea1n:\\r\\n- Hi\u1ec3u Blockchain l\xe0 g\xec\\r\\n- Hi\u1ec3u Web3 kh\xe1c Web2 \u1edf \u0111i\u1ec3m n\xe0o\\r\\n- Bi\u1ebft Smart Contract ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng ra sao\\r\\n- C\xf3 c\xe1i nh\xecn t\u1ed5ng quan tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi h\u1ecdc s\xe2u h\u01a1n\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udcca **Slide minh ho\u1ea1 to\xe0n b\u1ed9 b\xe0i h\u1ecdc:**  \\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 [Blockchain & Web3 \u2013 Canva](https://www.canva.com/design/DAHAWicpH1w/pfiXZRFKgXGG2dhy8E4q_g/edit?utm_content=DAHAWicpH1w&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link2&utm_source=sharebutton)\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Blockchain l\xe0 g\xec?\\r\\n\\r\\nBlockchain (chu\u1ed7i kh\u1ed1i) l\xe0 m\u1ed9t **c\u01a1 s\u1edf d\u1eef li\u1ec7u ph\xe2n t\xe1n**, n\u01a1i d\u1eef li\u1ec7u \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c:\\r\\n- Ghi l\u1ea1i th\xe0nh t\u1eebng **Block**\\r\\n- C\xe1c block **li\xean k\u1ebft v\u1edbi nhau b\u1eb1ng m\xe3 ho\xe1**\\r\\n- Kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 s\u1eeda \u0111\u1ed5i d\u1eef li\u1ec7u \u0111\xe3 ghi\\r\\n\\r\\n### \ud83d\udd17 \u0110\u1eb7c \u0111i\u1ec3m ch\xednh c\u1ee7a Blockchain\\r\\n- **Phi t\u1eadp trung**: Kh\xf4ng c\xf3 m\xe1y ch\u1ee7 trung t\xe2m\\r\\n- **Minh b\u1ea1ch**: Ai c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ki\u1ec3m tra giao d\u1ecbch\\r\\n- **B\u1ea5t bi\u1ebfn**: D\u1eef li\u1ec7u \u0111\xe3 ghi g\u1ea7n nh\u01b0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 xo\xe1\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udccc V\xed d\u1ee5:\\r\\n> Khi b\u1ea1n chuy\u1ec3n ti\u1ec1n tr\xean blockchain, giao d\u1ecbch \u0111\xf3 s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ghi l\u1ea1i v\u0129nh vi\u1ec5n v\xe0 m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u0111\u1ec1u c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ki\u1ec3m tra.\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 C\u1ea5u tr\xfac c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n c\u1ee7a Blockchain & Web3\\r\\n\\r\\nM\u1ed9t h\u1ec7 sinh th\xe1i Web3 th\u01b0\u1eddng g\u1ed3m c\xe1c th\xe0nh ph\u1ea7n sau:\\r\\n\\r\\n### \ud83d\udd39 Block\\r\\n- Ch\u1ee9a d\u1eef li\u1ec7u giao d\u1ecbch\\r\\n- C\xf3 m\xe3 b\u0103m (hash) c\u1ee7a block tr\u01b0\u1edbc\\r\\n\\r\\n### \ud83d\udd39 Hash\\r\\n- L\xe0 chu\u1ed7i k\xfd t\u1ef1 m\xe3 ho\xe1 \u0111\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho d\u1eef li\u1ec7u\\r\\n- Ch\u1ec9 c\u1ea7n thay \u0111\u1ed5i 1 k\xfd t\u1ef1 \u2192 hash \u0111\u1ed5i ho\xe0n to\xe0n\\r\\n\\r\\n### \ud83d\udd39 Node\\r\\n- L\xe0 c\xe1c m\xe1y t\xednh tham gia m\u1ea1ng blockchain\\r\\n- M\u1ed7i node l\u01b0u m\u1ed9t b\u1ea3n sao d\u1eef li\u1ec7u\\r\\n\\r\\n### \ud83d\udd39 Wallet (V\xed Web3)\\r\\n- \u0110\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho **danh t\xednh s\u1ed1** c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng\\r\\n- L\u01b0u private key (ch\xeca kho\xe1 ri\xeang)\\r\\n- V\xed d\u1ee5: MetaMask, Trust Wallet\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udcca **Slide minh ho\u1ea1 ph\u1ea7n c\u1ea5u tr\xfac:**  \\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 [Xem tr\xean Canva](https://www.canva.com/design/DAHAWicpH1w/pfiXZRFKgXGG2dhy8E4q_g/edit?utm_content=DAHAWicpH1w&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link2&utm_source=sharebutton)\\r\\n\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Smart Contract l\xe0 g\xec?\\r\\n\\r\\nSmart Contract (H\u1ee3p \u0111\u1ed3ng th\xf4ng minh) l\xe0:\\r\\n> **Ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\u1ea1y tr\xean blockchain**, kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n b\xean trung gian.\\r\\n\\r\\n### \ud83e\udde0 \u0110\u1eb7c \u0111i\u1ec3m\\r\\n- T\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng th\u1ef1c thi\\r\\n- Kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 ch\u1ec9nh s\u1eeda sau khi deploy\\r\\n- C\xf4ng khai & minh b\u1ea1ch\\r\\n\\r\\n### \u270d\ufe0f V\xed d\u1ee5 Smart Contract \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n (Solidity)\\r\\n\\r\\n```solidity\\r\\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\\r\\n\\r\\ncontract HelloWeb3 {\\r\\n    function hello() public pure returns(string memory) {\\r\\n        return \\"Hello Web3!\\";\\r\\n    }\\r\\n}"},{"id":"huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus","source":"@site/blog/blog/huong-dan-dung-blog.mdx","title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","description":"1. Blog l\xe0 g\xec? Docusaurus l\xe0 g\xec?","date":"2026-01-19T03:25:56.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.67,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","slug":"huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Blockchain & Web3 \u2013 H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1eeb c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n \u0111\u1ebfn th\u1ef1c h\xe0nh","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/blockchain-web3"},"nextItem":{"title":"Website","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/README"}},"content":"## 1. Blog l\xe0 g\xec? Docusaurus l\xe0 g\xec?\\r\\n\\r\\n**Blog** l\xe0 n\u01a1i chia s\u1ebb ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c, ghi ch\xe9p qu\xe1 tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp.  \\r\\n**Docusaurus** l\xe0 framework gi\xfap t\u1ea1o website blog / docs nhanh, \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng tr\xean React.\\r\\n\\r\\n## 2. C\xf4ng c\u1ee5 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng\\r\\n- NodeJS  \\r\\n- VS Code  \\r\\n- Docusaurus  \\r\\n- GitHub Pages  \\r\\n\\r\\n## 3. Quy tr\xecnh d\u1ef1ng Blog\\r\\n\\r\\nSlide d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y m\xf4 t\u1ea3 **to\xe0n b\u1ed9 quy tr\xecnh x\xe2y d\u1ef1ng website**,  \\r\\nt\u1eeb b\u01b0\u1edbc kh\u1edfi t\u1ea1o project cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi deploy (tri\u1ec3n khai) website l\xean GitHub Pages.\\r\\n\\r\\n\ud83d\udc49 **Xem slide h\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn chi ti\u1ebft t\u1ea1i \u0111\xe2y:**  \\r\\n\ud83d\udd17 https://www.canva.com/design/DAG-x-HN2J0/AXmxIe_VDDip6aalEPP8PQ/view\\r\\n\\r\\n*(Slide s\u1ebd m\u1edf \u1edf tab m\u1edbi \u0111\u1ec3 xem \u0111\u1ea7y \u0111\u1ee7 v\xe0 r\xf5 r\xe0ng h\u01a1n)*\\r\\n\\r\\n## 4. K\u1ebft lu\u1eadn\\r\\n\\r\\nSau khi xem slide, ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1edbi c\xf3 th\u1ec3:\\r\\n- T\u1ea1o project Docusaurus  \\r\\n- Vi\u1ebft b\xe0i blog  \\r\\n- \u0110\u1ea9y source code l\xean GitHub  \\r\\n- Deploy website b\u1eb1ng GitHub Pages"},{"id":"/README","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/README","source":"@site/blog/README.md","title":"Website","description":"This website is built using Docusaurus, a modern static website generator.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.56,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"H\u01b0\u1edbng d\u1eabn t\u1ea1o Blog b\u1eb1ng Docusaurus","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/huong-dan-tao-blog-docusaurus"},"nextItem":{"title":"blog/demo","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/demo"}},"content":"This website is built using [Docusaurus](https://docusaurus.io/), a modern static website generator.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Installation\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nyarn\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Local Development\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nyarn start\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThis command starts a local development server and opens up a browser window. Most changes are reflected live without having to restart the server.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Build\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nyarn build\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThis command generates static content into the `build` directory and can be served using any static contents hosting service.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Deployment\\r\\n\\r\\nUsing SSH:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nUSE_SSH=true yarn deploy\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nNot using SSH:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nGIT_USER=<Your GitHub username> yarn deploy\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you are using GitHub pages for hosting, this command is a convenient way to build the website and push to the `gh-pages` branch."},{"id":"/blog/demo","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/demo","source":"@site/blog/blog/demo.mdx","title":"blog/demo","description":"","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Website","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/README"},"nextItem":{"title":"Tutorial Intro","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/intro"}},"content":""},{"id":"/docs/intro","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/intro","source":"@site/blog/docs/intro.md","title":"Tutorial Intro","description":"Let\'s discover Docusaurus in less than 5 minutes.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":1},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"blog/demo","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/blog/demo"},"nextItem":{"title":"Congratulations!","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/congratulations"}},"content":"Let\'s discover **Docusaurus in less than 5 minutes**.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Getting Started\\r\\n\\r\\nGet started by **creating a new site**.\\r\\n\\r\\nOr **try Docusaurus immediately** with **[docusaurus.new](https://docusaurus.new)**.\\r\\n\\r\\n### What you\'ll need\\r\\n\\r\\n- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/download/) version 20.0 or above:\\r\\n  - When installing Node.js, you are recommended to check all checkboxes related to dependencies.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Generate a new site\\r\\n\\r\\nGenerate a new Docusaurus site using the **classic template**.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe classic template will automatically be added to your project after you run the command:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm init docusaurus@latest my-website classic\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can type this command into Command Prompt, Powershell, Terminal, or any other integrated terminal of your code editor.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe command also installs all necessary dependencies you need to run Docusaurus.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Start your site\\r\\n\\r\\nRun the development server:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncd my-website\\r\\nnpm run start\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThe `cd` command changes the directory you\'re working with. In order to work with your newly created Docusaurus site, you\'ll need to navigate the terminal there.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe `npm run start` command builds your website locally and serves it through a development server, ready for you to view at http://localhost:3000/.\\r\\n\\r\\nOpen `docs/intro.md` (this page) and edit some lines: the site **reloads automatically** and displays your changes."},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-basics/congratulations","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/congratulations","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/congratulations.md","title":"Congratulations!","description":"You have just learned the basics of Docusaurus and made some changes to the initial template.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.65,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":6},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Tutorial Intro","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/intro"},"nextItem":{"title":"Create a Blog Post","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-blog-post"}},"content":"You have just learned the **basics of Docusaurus** and made some changes to the **initial template**.\\r\\n\\r\\nDocusaurus has **much more to offer**!\\r\\n\\r\\nHave **5 more minutes**? Take a look at **[versioning](../tutorial-extras/manage-docs-versions.md)** and **[i18n](../tutorial-extras/translate-your-site.md)**.\\r\\n\\r\\nAnything **unclear** or **buggy** in this tutorial? [Please report it!](https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus/discussions/4610)\\r\\n\\r\\n## What\'s next?\\r\\n\\r\\n- Read the [official documentation](https://docusaurus.io/)\\r\\n- Modify your site configuration with [`docusaurus.config.js`](https://docusaurus.io/docs/api/docusaurus-config)\\r\\n- Add navbar and footer items with [`themeConfig`](https://docusaurus.io/docs/api/themes/configuration)\\r\\n- Add a custom [Design and Layout](https://docusaurus.io/docs/styling-layout)\\r\\n- Add a [search bar](https://docusaurus.io/docs/search)\\r\\n- Find inspirations in the [Docusaurus showcase](https://docusaurus.io/showcase)\\r\\n- Get involved in the [Docusaurus Community](https://docusaurus.io/community/support)"},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-blog-post","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-blog-post","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-blog-post.md","title":"Create a Blog Post","description":"Docusaurus creates a page for each blog post, but also a blog index page, a tag system, an RSS feed...","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.58,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":3},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Congratulations!","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/congratulations"},"nextItem":{"title":"Create a Document","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-document"}},"content":"Docusaurus creates a **page for each blog post**, but also a **blog index page**, a **tag system**, an **RSS** feed...\\r\\n\\r\\n## Create your first Post\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate a file at `blog/2021-02-28-greetings.md`:\\r\\n\\r\\n```md title=\\"blog/2021-02-28-greetings.md\\"\\r\\n---\\r\\nslug: greetings\\r\\ntitle: Greetings!\\r\\nauthors:\\r\\n  - name: Joel Marcey\\r\\n    title: Co-creator of Docusaurus 1\\r\\n    url: https://github.com/JoelMarcey\\r\\n    image_url: https://github.com/JoelMarcey.png\\r\\n  - name: S\xe9bastien Lorber\\r\\n    title: Docusaurus maintainer\\r\\n    url: https://sebastienlorber.com\\r\\n    image_url: https://github.com/slorber.png\\r\\ntags: [greetings]\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\nCongratulations, you have made your first post!\\r\\n\\r\\nFeel free to play around and edit this post as much as you like.\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nA new blog post is now available at [http://localhost:3000/blog/greetings](http://localhost:3000/blog/greetings)."},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-document","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-document","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-document.md","title":"Create a Document","description":"Documents are groups of pages connected through:","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.61,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":2},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Create a Blog Post","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-blog-post"},"nextItem":{"title":"Create a Page","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-page"}},"content":"Documents are **groups of pages** connected through:\\r\\n\\r\\n- a **sidebar**\\r\\n- **previous/next navigation**\\r\\n- **versioning**\\r\\n\\r\\n## Create your first Doc\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate a Markdown file at `docs/hello.md`:\\r\\n\\r\\n```md title=\\"docs/hello.md\\"\\r\\n# Hello\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is my **first Docusaurus document**!\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nA new document is now available at [http://localhost:3000/docs/hello](http://localhost:3000/docs/hello).\\r\\n\\r\\n## Configure the Sidebar\\r\\n\\r\\nDocusaurus automatically **creates a sidebar** from the `docs` folder.\\r\\n\\r\\nAdd metadata to customize the sidebar label and position:\\r\\n\\r\\n```md title=\\"docs/hello.md\\" {1-4}\\r\\n---\\r\\nsidebar_label: \'Hi!\'\\r\\nsidebar_position: 3\\r\\n---\\r\\n\\r\\n# Hello\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is my **first Docusaurus document**!\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is also possible to create your sidebar explicitly in `sidebars.js`:\\r\\n\\r\\n```js title=\\"sidebars.js\\"\\r\\nexport default {\\r\\n  tutorialSidebar: [\\r\\n    \'intro\',\\r\\n    // highlight-next-line\\r\\n    \'hello\',\\r\\n    {\\r\\n      type: \'category\',\\r\\n      label: \'Tutorial\',\\r\\n      items: [\'tutorial-basics/create-a-document\'],\\r\\n    },\\r\\n  ],\\r\\n};\\r\\n```"},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-page","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-page","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-page.md","title":"Create a Page","description":"Add Markdown or React files to src/pages to create a standalone page:","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.74,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":1},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Create a Document","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-document"},"nextItem":{"title":"Deploy your site","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/deploy-your-site"}},"content":"Add **Markdown or React** files to `src/pages` to create a **standalone page**:\\r\\n\\r\\n- `src/pages/index.js` \u2192 `localhost:3000/`\\r\\n- `src/pages/foo.md` \u2192 `localhost:3000/foo`\\r\\n- `src/pages/foo/bar.js` \u2192 `localhost:3000/foo/bar`\\r\\n\\r\\n## Create your first React Page\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate a file at `src/pages/my-react-page.js`:\\r\\n\\r\\n```jsx title=\\"src/pages/my-react-page.js\\"\\r\\nimport React from \'react\';\\r\\nimport Layout from \'@theme/Layout\';\\r\\n\\r\\nexport default function MyReactPage() {\\r\\n  return (\\r\\n    <Layout>\\r\\n      <h1>My React page</h1>\\r\\n      <p>This is a React page</p>\\r\\n    </Layout>\\r\\n  );\\r\\n}\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nA new page is now available at [http://localhost:3000/my-react-page](http://localhost:3000/my-react-page).\\r\\n\\r\\n## Create your first Markdown Page\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate a file at `src/pages/my-markdown-page.md`:\\r\\n\\r\\n```mdx title=\\"src/pages/my-markdown-page.md\\"\\r\\n# My Markdown page\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is a Markdown page\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nA new page is now available at [http://localhost:3000/my-markdown-page](http://localhost:3000/my-markdown-page)."},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-basics/deploy-your-site","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/deploy-your-site","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/deploy-your-site.md","title":"Deploy your site","description":"Docusaurus is a static-site-generator (also called Jamstack).","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.47,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":5},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Create a Page","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/create-a-page"},"nextItem":{"title":"Markdown Features","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/markdown-features"}},"content":"Docusaurus is a **static-site-generator** (also called **[Jamstack](https://jamstack.org/)**).\\r\\n\\r\\nIt builds your site as simple **static HTML, JavaScript and CSS files**.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Build your site\\r\\n\\r\\nBuild your site **for production**:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm run build\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThe static files are generated in the `build` folder.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Deploy your site\\r\\n\\r\\nTest your production build locally:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm run serve\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThe `build` folder is now served at [http://localhost:3000/](http://localhost:3000/).\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can now deploy the `build` folder **almost anywhere** easily, **for free** or very small cost (read the **[Deployment Guide](https://docusaurus.io/docs/deployment)**)."},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-basics/markdown-features","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/markdown-features","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/markdown-features.mdx","title":"Markdown Features","description":"Docusaurus supports Markdown and a few additional features.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.78,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":4},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Deploy your site","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/deploy-your-site"},"nextItem":{"title":"Manage Docs Versions","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/manage-docs-versions"}},"content":"Docusaurus supports **[Markdown](https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax)** and a few **additional features**.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Front Matter\\r\\n\\r\\nMarkdown documents have metadata at the top called [Front Matter](https://jekyllrb.com/docs/front-matter/):\\r\\n\\r\\n```text title=\\"my-doc.md\\"\\r\\n// highlight-start\\r\\n---\\r\\nid: my-doc-id\\r\\ntitle: My document title\\r\\ndescription: My document description\\r\\nslug: /my-custom-url\\r\\n---\\r\\n// highlight-end\\r\\n\\r\\n## Markdown heading\\r\\n\\r\\nMarkdown text with [links](./hello.md)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Links\\r\\n\\r\\nRegular Markdown links are supported, using url paths or relative file paths.\\r\\n\\r\\n```md\\r\\nLet\'s see how to [Create a page](/create-a-page).\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n```md\\r\\nLet\'s see how to [Create a page](./create-a-page.md).\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n**Result:** Let\'s see how to [Create a page](./create-a-page.md).\\r\\n\\r\\n## Images\\r\\n\\r\\nRegular Markdown images are supported.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can use absolute paths to reference images in the static directory (`static/img/docusaurus.png`):\\r\\n\\r\\n```md\\r\\n![Docusaurus logo](/img/docusaurus.png)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n![Docusaurus logo](/img/docusaurus.png)\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can reference images relative to the current file as well. This is particularly useful to colocate images close to the Markdown files using them:\\r\\n\\r\\n```md\\r\\n![Docusaurus logo](./img/docusaurus.png)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Code Blocks\\r\\n\\r\\nMarkdown code blocks are supported with Syntax highlighting.\\r\\n\\r\\n````md\\r\\n```jsx title=\\"src/components/HelloDocusaurus.js\\"\\r\\nfunction HelloDocusaurus() {\\r\\n  return <h1>Hello, Docusaurus!</h1>;\\r\\n}\\r\\n```\\r\\n````\\r\\n\\r\\n```jsx title=\\"src/components/HelloDocusaurus.js\\"\\r\\nfunction HelloDocusaurus() {\\r\\n  return <h1>Hello, Docusaurus!</h1>;\\r\\n}\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Admonitions\\r\\n\\r\\nDocusaurus has a special syntax to create admonitions and callouts:\\r\\n\\r\\n```md\\r\\n:::tip My tip\\r\\n\\r\\nUse this awesome feature option\\r\\n\\r\\n:::\\r\\n\\r\\n:::danger Take care\\r\\n\\r\\nThis action is dangerous\\r\\n\\r\\n:::\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n:::tip My tip\\r\\n\\r\\nUse this awesome feature option\\r\\n\\r\\n:::\\r\\n\\r\\n:::danger Take care\\r\\n\\r\\nThis action is dangerous\\r\\n\\r\\n:::\\r\\n\\r\\n## MDX and React Components\\r\\n\\r\\n[MDX](https://mdxjs.com/) can make your documentation more **interactive** and allows using any **React components inside Markdown**:\\r\\n\\r\\n```jsx\\r\\nexport const Highlight = ({children, color}) => (\\r\\n  <span\\r\\n    style={{\\r\\n      backgroundColor: color,\\r\\n      borderRadius: \'20px\',\\r\\n      color: \'#fff\',\\r\\n      padding: \'10px\',\\r\\n      cursor: \'pointer\',\\r\\n    }}\\r\\n    onClick={() => {\\r\\n      alert(`You clicked the color ${color} with label ${children}`)\\r\\n    }}>\\r\\n    {children}\\r\\n  </span>\\r\\n);\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is <Highlight color=\\"#25c2a0\\">Docusaurus green</Highlight> !\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is <Highlight color=\\"#1877F2\\">Facebook blue</Highlight> !\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nexport const Highlight = ({children, color}) => (\\r\\n  <span\\r\\n    style={{\\r\\n      backgroundColor: color,\\r\\n      borderRadius: \'20px\',\\r\\n      color: \'#fff\',\\r\\n      padding: \'10px\',\\r\\n      cursor: \'pointer\',\\r\\n    }}\\r\\n    onClick={() => {\\r\\n      alert(`You clicked the color ${color} with label ${children}`);\\r\\n    }}>\\r\\n    {children}\\r\\n  </span>\\r\\n);\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is <Highlight color=\\"#25c2a0\\">Docusaurus green</Highlight> !\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is <Highlight color=\\"#1877F2\\">Facebook blue</Highlight> !"},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-extras/manage-docs-versions","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/manage-docs-versions","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/manage-docs-versions.md","title":"Manage Docs Versions","description":"Docusaurus can manage multiple versions of your docs.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.73,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":1},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Markdown Features","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-basics/markdown-features"},"nextItem":{"title":"Translate your site","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/translate-your-site"}},"content":"Docusaurus can manage multiple versions of your docs.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Create a docs version\\r\\n\\r\\nRelease a version 1.0 of your project:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm run docusaurus docs:version 1.0\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThe `docs` folder is copied into `versioned_docs/version-1.0` and `versions.json` is created.\\r\\n\\r\\nYour docs now have 2 versions:\\r\\n\\r\\n- `1.0` at `http://localhost:3000/docs/` for the version 1.0 docs\\r\\n- `current` at `http://localhost:3000/docs/next/` for the **upcoming, unreleased docs**\\r\\n\\r\\n## Add a Version Dropdown\\r\\n\\r\\nTo navigate seamlessly across versions, add a version dropdown.\\r\\n\\r\\nModify the `docusaurus.config.js` file:\\r\\n\\r\\n```js title=\\"docusaurus.config.js\\"\\r\\nexport default {\\r\\n  themeConfig: {\\r\\n    navbar: {\\r\\n      items: [\\r\\n        // highlight-start\\r\\n        {\\r\\n          type: \'docsVersionDropdown\',\\r\\n        },\\r\\n        // highlight-end\\r\\n      ],\\r\\n    },\\r\\n  },\\r\\n};\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThe docs version dropdown appears in your navbar:\\r\\n\\r\\n![Docs Version Dropdown](./img/docsVersionDropdown.png)\\r\\n\\r\\n## Update an existing version\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is possible to edit versioned docs in their respective folder:\\r\\n\\r\\n- `versioned_docs/version-1.0/hello.md` updates `http://localhost:3000/docs/hello`\\r\\n- `docs/hello.md` updates `http://localhost:3000/docs/next/hello`"},{"id":"/docs/tutorial-extras/translate-your-site","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/translate-your-site","source":"@site/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/translate-your-site.md","title":"Translate your site","description":"Let\'s translate docs/intro.md to French.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.99,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"sidebar_position":2},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Manage Docs Versions","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/manage-docs-versions"},"nextItem":{"title":"Markdown page example","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/src/pages/markdown-page"}},"content":"Let\'s translate `docs/intro.md` to French.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Configure i18n\\r\\n\\r\\nModify `docusaurus.config.js` to add support for the `fr` locale:\\r\\n\\r\\n```js title=\\"docusaurus.config.js\\"\\r\\nexport default {\\r\\n  i18n: {\\r\\n    defaultLocale: \'en\',\\r\\n    locales: [\'en\', \'fr\'],\\r\\n  },\\r\\n};\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Translate a doc\\r\\n\\r\\nCopy the `docs/intro.md` file to the `i18n/fr` folder:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nmkdir -p i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current/\\r\\n\\r\\ncp docs/intro.md i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current/intro.md\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nTranslate `i18n/fr/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current/intro.md` in French.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Start your localized site\\r\\n\\r\\nStart your site on the French locale:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm run start -- --locale fr\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nYour localized site is accessible at [http://localhost:3000/fr/](http://localhost:3000/fr/) and the `Getting Started` page is translated.\\r\\n\\r\\n:::caution\\r\\n\\r\\nIn development, you can only use one locale at a time.\\r\\n\\r\\n:::\\r\\n\\r\\n## Add a Locale Dropdown\\r\\n\\r\\nTo navigate seamlessly across languages, add a locale dropdown.\\r\\n\\r\\nModify the `docusaurus.config.js` file:\\r\\n\\r\\n```js title=\\"docusaurus.config.js\\"\\r\\nexport default {\\r\\n  themeConfig: {\\r\\n    navbar: {\\r\\n      items: [\\r\\n        // highlight-start\\r\\n        {\\r\\n          type: \'localeDropdown\',\\r\\n        },\\r\\n        // highlight-end\\r\\n      ],\\r\\n    },\\r\\n  },\\r\\n};\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThe locale dropdown now appears in your navbar:\\r\\n\\r\\n![Locale Dropdown](./img/localeDropdown.png)\\r\\n\\r\\n## Build your localized site\\r\\n\\r\\nBuild your site for a specific locale:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm run build -- --locale fr\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nOr build your site to include all the locales at once:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm run build\\r\\n```"},{"id":"/src/pages/markdown-page","metadata":{"permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/src/pages/markdown-page","source":"@site/blog/src/pages/markdown-page.md","title":"Markdown page example","description":"You don\'t need React to write simple standalone pages.","date":"2026-01-15T05:38:02.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.05,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Markdown page example"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Translate your site","permalink":"/my-docusaurus/blog/docs/tutorial-extras/translate-your-site"}},"content":"You don\'t need React to write simple standalone pages."}]}}')}}]);